<!--
  SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0

  vibemix — macOS Hardened Runtime DISTRIBUTION entitlements
  Bundle ID: world.bravoh.vibemix (LOCKED — see 11-RESEARCH.md §A8)

  macOS TCC permissions (Screen Recording, Microphone, Accessibility) are
  keyed to the bundle identifier. Any post-launch change to
  ``world.bravoh.vibemix`` invalidates every user's previously-granted
  permissions and force-prompts the system modal again — that's a
  release-grade regression. The lock is enforced here, in
  ``tauri/src-tauri/entitlements.plist`` (Phase 11 build-time plist),
  ``tauri/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json5`` (the bundle identifier),
  ``vibemix-core.macos.spec`` (PyInstaller spec), and
  ``scripts/dist/sign_macos.sh`` (this file's consumer).

  Reference: 18-CONTEXT.md §Area 2 — macOS Signing + Notarization
  Reference: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/security/hardened_runtime

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  This is the DISTRIBUTION-grade entitlements file. It is consumed by
  ``scripts/dist/sign_macos.sh`` AFTER the bundle has been built, via:
      codesign --force --deep --options runtime \
               --entitlements tauri/src-tauri/entitlements.macos.plist \
               --timestamp <app-bundle>

  The sibling ``tauri/src-tauri/entitlements.plist`` (Phase 11 W1) is the
  BUILD-time entitlements used by ``cargo tauri build`` for its own
  Tauri-wrapper signing pass. That file ships with FOUR entitlements:
      audio-input, microphone, allow-unsigned-executable-memory,
      disable-library-validation
  This file ships with FIVE per CONTEXT D-Area-2:
      audio-input, microphone, network.client, allow-jit,
      allow-unsigned-executable-memory

  Deltas vs Phase 11 build-time plist:
    (+) network.client — explicit. Phase 5 proxy at api.altidus.world +
        Tauri auto-updater (Plan 18-04) + every outbound Gemini call.
        Phase 11 had it implicit; distribution-grade requires it explicit.
    (+) allow-jit — Python interpreter on macOS 14+. Phase 11's plist
        explicitly excluded JIT ("we don't run a JIT") on the grounds
        that CPython is interpreted and numpy/scipy are AOT-compiled C.
        CONTEXT D-Area-2 overrides this: ``livekit-agents`` JIT-compiles
        regex patterns at startup, and macOS 14+ rejects the launch
        without ``allow-jit``. This is the documented deviation. If a
        signing run later proves JIT is NOT needed, drop it — keep the
        plist minimal.
    (-) disable-library-validation — Phase 11 had it for the .dylibs that
        third parties (livekit-rtc, google-genai, sounddevice) sign with
        their own identities. CONTEXT D-Area-2 explicitly drops it from
        the 5-entitlement allowlist. Plan 18-05 wires the CI signing run
        that surfaces any library-validation failure deterministically;
        if a real failure shows up there, the fix is a docketed amendment
        to CONTEXT D-Area-2, not a silent re-addition here.

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  WHY each entitlement (one paragraph each):

  1. com.apple.security.device.audio-input
     BlackHole 2ch virtual-audio loopback (Master capture) + Kaan's mic
     for the KAAN_SPOKE detector. Without this, the OS returns silence
     from CoreAudio when ``sounddevice`` opens the BlackHole input device,
     and the whole reaction pipeline goes dark.

  2. com.apple.security.device.microphone
     User-facing TCC prompt for "vibemix would like to access the
     microphone". Kaan's wizard Step 1 (Phase 11) triggers this; the live
     session uses it for KAAN_SPOKE feedback gating.

  3. com.apple.security.network.client
     Outbound HTTPS to api.altidus.world (Phase 5 proxy — every LLM call,
     every TTS call, every cohost generate_reply) + Tauri auto-updater
     manifest fetch (Plan 18-04) + GitHub Releases redirect chase for
     update payload download. No inbound listening — vibemix is a
     localhost-only single-user app, no server posture.

  4. com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
     Python interpreter on macOS 14+. The launch-time JIT path is hit by
     livekit-agents' regex compiler and by a handful of third-party deps
     that build trampolines at import. macOS 14+ rejects the launch with
     a misleading "code signature invalid" error if this entitlement is
     missing on a Hardened-Runtime + Notarized build. Documented as a
     deviation from Phase 11's "no JIT" note (see header).

  5. com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
     PyInstaller's bootloader runs C extensions (scipy, numpy,
     sounddevice native libs, livekit_rtc.dylib) that allocate
     writable+executable memory pages OUTSIDE the bundle's signed code
     segment. Without this, Hardened Runtime kills the process the first
     time numpy initializes its BLAS dispatcher.

  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  WHAT IS DELIBERATELY NOT INCLUDED:

  - The "app sandbox" key (deliberately NOT listed below)
     BlackHole virtual-audio + global hotkeys (Phase 12's keyboard
     shortcut for "manual trigger") break inside the sandbox. The OS
     refuses to route audio through a virtual driver to a sandboxed app,
     and sandboxed apps cannot register system-wide hotkeys. CONTEXT
     D-Area-2 explicit. The price is no Mac App Store; the entire OSS
     distribution channel is GitHub Releases (signed DMG + Sparkle-style
     updater), so this is an accepted trade.

  - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
     Phase 11's build-time entitlements.plist includes it. This
     distribution plist drops it per CONTEXT D-Area-2's 5-entitlement
     allowlist. If a real signing run shows that PyInstaller's
     _internal/ tree cannot load its bundled .dylibs without this,
     Plan 18-05's CI surfaces the failure deterministically (spctl
     reject + notarytool log dump). The remediation is a docketed
     amendment to CONTEXT D-Area-2, not a silent re-addition.

  - camera / address-book / location / get-task-allow
     Zero use cases. The mascot is a rendered 3D character (Phase 13),
     not a camera feed.

  - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables
     Plain unnecessary for the runtime. PyInstaller does its own
     PYTHONPATH bookkeeping inside the bundle.

  THREAT MODEL (per 18-02-PLAN.md threat_model):
    T-18-05 (Spoofing of signed .dmg): mitigated by Apple Developer ID +
            Hardened Runtime + notarization + stapler — the standard
            macOS chain. spctl-assess gate is Stage 7 of sign_macos.sh.
    T-18-08 (Elevation of Privilege via entitlement bloat): the file is
            committed; PR review catches additions. CI verifies the
            entitlement count equals exactly 5 (Plan 18-05 wires the
            regression detector).
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- 1. Audio capture: BlackHole loopback (master output) + Kaan's mic -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- 2. Microphone: user-facing TCC prompt; KAAN_SPOKE detector source -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.microphone</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- 3. Network client: Phase 5 proxy + Tauri auto-updater + Gemini calls.
              No server posture — outbound HTTPS only. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- 4. JIT executable memory: livekit-agents + other deps compile
              regex / trampolines at import. macOS 14+ rejects launch
              without this on Hardened-Runtime builds. Deviation from
              Phase 11's "no JIT" note — see header. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- 5. Unsigned executable memory: PyInstaller bootloader + numpy /
              scipy / sounddevice native libs allocate W+X pages outside
              the signed code segment. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
